Regular expressions should not contain multiple spaces
Why is this an issue? Multiple spaces in a regular expression can make it hard to tell how many spaces should be matched. Itâ€™s more readable to use only one space and then indicate with a quantifier how many spaces are expected. 
### Noncompliant
Pattern.compile("hello   world");
### Compliant
Pattern.compile("hello {3}world");
### Noncompliant
{{BUGGY}}
